    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "### Ways to Structure Code inside the \"Random\" block \r\nThere are four different C-shaped blocks you can use to help structure your code inside the `random` block. \r\n- `play together`\r\n- `play sequential`\r\n- `repeat`\r\n- `random` (yes, another random in a random!) \r\n\r\n**Do This:**\r\n- Add at least 2 sounds to each of the C-shaped blocks in your start code. \r\n- Keep pressing \"Run\" until all possible options are complete. \r\n- *Bonus: Add a few sounds into the `play random` block without any C-shaped blocks around it. What happens?*",
